'''梧桐树协议'''（Buttonwood Agreement），是[[美国|美国]][[纽约市|纽约市]]24家[[证券经纪人|股票经纪商]]于1792年5月17日在[[华尔街|华尔街]]68号门外的一棵[[美桐|美國梧桐]]下订立的协议，被认为是[[纽约股票交易所|纽约股票交易所]]规程的起源。<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://time.com/4777959/buttonwood-agreement-stock-exchange/ | title=''How a Financial Panic Helped Launch the New York Stock Exchange'' | author=Olivia B. Waxman | publisher=time.com | accessdate=2017-05-17 | archive-date=2017-05-17 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170517140916/http://time.com/4777959/buttonwood-agreement-stock-exchange/ | dead-url=no }}{{en}}</ref>

==协议==
梧桐树协议确立了两个重要原则：
# 股票经纪人只能与其他经纪人进行交易
# 股票交易佣金不得低于0.25%

协议的内容为：
{{cquote|吾等，作为签名者和公开证券的购买和销售经理人，在此庄重承诺并向彼此保证：自今天起无论如何也不会买卖任何低于委托价值的0.25%的任何种类证券，且吾等会在交易中给予彼此优先权。特此立据于1792年5月17日之纽约。<ref name="Teweles1992">{{cite book|title=The Stock Market (6th Edition) |date=1992|pages=97頁 |author=Richard J. Teweles, Edward S. Bradley, and Ted M. Teweles}}</ref>}}

英语原文如下：
{{cquote|We the Subscribers, Brokers for the Purchase and Sale of the Public Stock, do hereby solemnly promise and pledge ourselves to each other, that we will not buy or sell from this day for any person whatsoever, any kind of Public Stock, at least than one quarter per cent Commission on the Specie value and that we will give preference to each other in our Negotiations. In Testimony whereof we have set our hands this 17th day of May at New York, 1792.<ref name="Teweles1992"/>}}

